headline: OpenAI’s New Fundraising Round Could Value Startup at as Much as $830 Billion
summary: Chief Executive  Sam Altman  has already scoured the world to build the pool of OpenAI’s investors and the company is now weighing a potential initial public offering, The Wall Street Journal previously reported.  The company has faced skepticism over computing deals it has forged that are worth hundreds of billions of dollars and issued a “code red” to beat back a growing threat from Google.

headline: Disney Stock Is This Analyst’s Top Media Pick. Why It Can Bounce Back.
summary: Wells Fargo has named  Walt Disney  its top media stock for 2026, in a bet that the company’s streaming, theme park, and cruise businesses will see growth.  Analyst Steven Cahall moved  Disney  to the No. one slot in a research note Thursday, replacing  Spotify Technology  He’s confident in theme park growth—despite competition and possible consumer spending pull backs—and is optimistic that streaming margins and box-office performance will grow.  Shares of Disney were up 1% to $111.82 on Thursday.
